The paper deals with the parallelization of a fast Fourier transform algorithm, which is a numerical method used in scientific computing. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses the OpenMP standard for parallelization, which is commonly used in shared-memory parallel programming, further supporting cs.DC as a likely category. The paper also mentions a geometric approach and symmetries of the underlying basis functions, which could relate to Computational Geometry (cs.CG) or Mathematical Software (cs.MS). Overall, cs.NA and cs.DC seem to be the most likely categories, followed by cs.SC, cs.CG, and cs.MS.
